The paper deals with the problem of embedding graphs into simpler metrics, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper also mentions approximation algorithms and fixed-parameter tractable algorithms, which are common techniques used in algorithm design and analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and computational complexity, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
